#: ../../docs/classes/class_audioeffectdistortion.rst:57
msgid ""
"**MODE_CLIP** = **0** --- Digital distortion effect which cuts off peaks "
"at the top and bottom of the waveform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_audioeffectdistortion.rst:59
msgid "**MODE_ATAN** = **1**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_audioeffectdistortion.rst:61
msgid ""
"**MODE_LOFI** = **2** --- Low-resolution digital distortion effect. You "
"can use it to emulate the sound of early digital audio devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_audioeffectdistortion.rst:63
msgid ""
"**MODE_OVERDRIVE** = **3** --- Emulates the warm distortion produced by a"
" field effect transistor, which is commonly used in solid-state musical "
"instrument amplifiers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_audioeffectdistortion.rst:65
msgid ""
"**MODE_WAVESHAPE** = **4** --- Waveshaper distortions are used mainly by "
"electronic musicians to achieve an extra-abrasive sound."
msgstr ""

